---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/base_layout.astro";

const base = "/projects/monolith_for_light";
const title = "Monolith for Light";
---

<BaseLayout title={`${title} — Dai Pan`} active="gallery_design">
    <article class="gallery">
        <!-- 首段：图左文右 -->
        <section class="gallery__section gallery__intro-row">
            <figure class="gallery__figure gallery__intro-figure">
                <img
                    src={`${base}/gallery_01.jpg`}
                    alt="Monolith for Light — atmosphere and massing (01)"
                    loading="eager"
                />
            </figure>
            <div class="gallery__text gallery__intro-text">
                <p>
                    Monolith for Light is a study of mass and restraint in an open, barren field.
                    The building is held as one dense body—concrete and limestone. No glass, so daylight arrives only through cuts.
                    Light is not added. It becomes measure: a line, a depth, a duration.
                    What seems like darkness is simply the space waiting to be read.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Inspired by <em>In Praise of Shadows</em>, the project explores
                    how atmosphere can be built through restraint. Shadows are treated as structure. The design
                    studies light as structure—how it frames movement, sets tempo,
                    and produces "rooms" that are defined by time rather than by
                    decoration.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="gallery__section">
            <p class="gallery__text">
                Plan, elevation, and section establish the controlled cuts and
                the internal sequence as a spatial narrative rather than a
                transparent container.
            </p>
            <figure class="gallery__figure gallery__figure--compact">
                <img
                    src={`${base}/gallery_02.jpg`}
                    alt="Plan / elevation / section (02)"
                    loading="lazy"
                />
            </figure>
            <figure class="gallery__figure gallery__figure--compact">
                <img
                    src={`${base}/gallery_03.jpg`}
                    alt="Sectional study (03)"
                    loading="lazy"
                />
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section class="gallery__section">
            <p class="gallery__text">
                The project frames the landscape as part of the gallery
                experience—orientation, horizon lines, and the way wind and
                sun set up a "reading" of the building before entry.
            </p>
            <p class="gallery__text">
                At night, concealed lighting returns the same cuts and edges
                as a new structure. The mass remains unchanged, but its
                hierarchy is rewritten by illumination.
            </p>
            <figure class="gallery__figure gallery__figure--compact">
                <img
                    src={`${base}/gallery_05.jpg`}
                    alt="Site / horizon study (05)"
                    loading="lazy"
                />
            </figure>
            <figure class="gallery__figure gallery__figure--compact">
                <img
                    src={`${base}/gallery_06.jpg`}
                    alt="Night exterior (06)"
                    loading="lazy"
                />
            </figure>
            <figure class="gallery__figure">
                <img
                    src={`${base}/gallery_09.jpg`}
                    alt="Exploded axonometric (07)"
                    loading="lazy"
                />
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section class="gallery__section">
            <p class="gallery__text">
                A corridor becomes a measuring device: thin slits and angled
                surfaces turn light into direction, duration, and
                pressure—guiding how long the visitor lingers and what
                becomes visible.
            </p>
            <figure class="gallery__figure gallery__figure--compact">
                <img
                    src={`${base}/gallery_07.jpg`}
                    alt="Interior gallery (07)"
                    loading="lazy"
                />
            </figure>
            <figure class="gallery__figure gallery__figure--compact">
                <img
                    src={`${base}/gallery_08.jpg`}
                    alt="Interior corridor (08)"
                    loading="lazy"
                />
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section class="gallery__section">
            <p class="gallery__text">
                A sectional view clarifies how the interior voids are carved
                and how the building holds darkness as a deliberate spatial
                condition. The final diagram summarizes circulation and
                service logic, separating visitor movement from staff access
                and maintenance routes.
            </p>
            <div class="gallery__grid2">
                <figure class="gallery__tile">
                    <img
                        src={`${base}/gallery_11.jpg`}
                        alt="Section perspective (11)"
                        loading="lazy"
                    />
                </figure>
                <figure class="gallery__tile">
                    <img
                        src={`${base}/gallery_10.jpg`}
                        alt="Material / detail study (09)"
                        loading="lazy"
                    />
                </figure>
            </div>
            <figure class="gallery__figure">
                <img
                    src={`${base}/gallery_04.jpg`}
                    alt="Flow / access diagram (04)"
                    loading="lazy"
                />
            </figure>
        </section>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    /* 与 the_threes 一致：section 间距 56px，块内 18px */
    .gallery {
        --gallery-max: min(832px, 100%);
        --gallery-intro-max: min(960px, 100%);
    }

    .gallery__section + .gallery__section {
        margin-top: 0;
    }

    /* section 底部分割线，空档更自然 */
    .gallery__section:not(:last-child) {
        padding-bottom: 40px;
    }

    .gallery__section > * + * {
        margin-top: 18px;
    }

    /* 首段：图左文右。调大 gallery_01：改 grid 比例；让文字更贴图：改小 gap */
    .gallery__intro-row {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 0.7fr;
        gap: 0; /* 图与文字的横向间距，只能填正数（0、8、12…），负值无效 */
        align-items: start;
        max-width: var(--gallery-intro-max);
        margin-inline: auto;
    }

    .gallery__intro-row .gallery__intro-figure {
        margin: 0;
    }

    .gallery__intro-row .gallery__intro-figure img {
        max-width: 100%;
        display: block;
    }

    /* 首段右侧描述：负 margin-left 把段落往左拉，更贴图；可改 padding-top 调节与顶部的距离 */
    .gallery__intro-row .gallery__intro-text {
        margin: 0 0 0 -48px; /* 负值越大越贴图，不够近可改为 -40px / -48px */
        padding-top: 42px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 700px) {
        .gallery__intro-row {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            gap: 18px;
        }
    }

    /* 正文：与 the_threes .threes__text-wrap 一致 */
    .gallery__text {
        margin: 0;
        max-width: 70ch;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        line-height: 1.78;
        color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.78);
    }

    .gallery__text p {
        margin: 0 0 18px;
    }

    .gallery__text p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    /* 单图 */
    .gallery__figure {
        margin: 0;
    }

    .gallery__figure img {
        display: block;
        max-width: var(--gallery-max);
        max-height: min(68vh, 720px);
        width: auto;
        height: auto;
        object-fit: contain;
        margin-inline: 0; /* 与上方文字左边缘对齐 */
        filter: brightness(0.96);
        transition: transform 700ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.6, 0.2, 1);
        transform: translateZ(0);
    }

    .gallery__figure:hover img {
        transform: scale(1.03);
        filter: brightness(1);
    }

    /* 02、03、05、06、07、08 六张图缩小约 12%，页面更紧凑 */
    .gallery__figure--compact img {
        max-width: min(732px, 88%);
        max-height: min(60vh, 612px);
    }

    /* 双图网格 */
    .gallery__grid2 {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
        gap: 18px;
        max-width: var(--gallery-max);
        margin-inline: 0; /* 与上方文字左边缘对齐 */
    }

    .gallery__tile {
        margin: 0;
        width: 100%;
        aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03);
    }

    .gallery__tile img {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
        display: block;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
        .gallery__grid2 {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
    }

    @media (hover: hover) and (pointer: fine) {
        .gallery__figure,
        .gallery__tile {
            overflow: hidden;
        }
    }

    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
        .gallery__figure img,
        .gallery__tile img {
            transition: none;
        }
    }
</style>
